2.01	Ox-Cart_Man	Ox-Cart Man	Ox-Cart Man is the title of a 1979 book written by Donald Hall and illustrated by Barbara Cooney. It won the 1980 Caldecott Medal. The book deals with an 18th century farming family that uses an ox-cart to take their goods to market, where they make the money to buy the things they need.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/d/d5/Oxcartman-1-.gif
